They’re here!! So happy to finally introduce Asher Shalom & Zion Shalom Arnold! 💙🩵

Asher Shalom (Baby A) 8 pounds 5oz 20.5” long 9:08am 6/22/23

Zion Shalom (Baby 😎  7 pounds 11 oz 20.5” long 9:07 am 6/22/23

The birth plan didn’t quite go as planned but we are over joyed with our 2 perfect boys! I had 2 castor oil shakes before going into the hospital and a ton of Pitocin at the hospital and after 36 hours of labor, the contractions weren’t consistent enough and after trying an exhaustive list of still trying to have a natural birth, our last option was a c-section and that’s what ended up happening. Basically what was  happening is Baby A was head down and in the birth canal (I was 8cm dilated) but at a weird angle and Baby B was completely transverse aka sideways so it was making my uterus a wonkey shape and pushing A to the side preventing the contractions from properly moving the babies down. Luckily both babies were doing great throughout this trial and error process so they weren’t under any stress…just me 😅 The c-section went well and all of us are doing great! Thank you to everyone for the continued prayers! We may not have had the birth experience we wanted but we ultimately have what we wanted…. Healthy baby boys! 💙🩵

#newtwinmom #twinmom #boymom #birthstory #newborntwins #csection #inlove
